abstract: Instead of just watching historic homes plunge into foreclosure and collapse, some residents decided to buy and rehabilitate them.
snippet: Instead of just watching historic homes plunge into foreclosure and collapse, some residents decided to buy and rehabilitate them.
lead_paragraph: SOUTH BEND, Ind. — When the grand Queen Anne on Portage Avenue lost its last occupants a few years ago, plunging into foreclosure and abandonment, the century-old gem risked the same fate as hundreds of empty houses here: collapse or demolition. Either way, what had been a lumber baron’s masterpiece was bound to become just another forgotten lot on the Rust Belt.

abstract: On an unexpectedly warm November day, lunch outdoors meant takeout, brown-bag fare and a good view.
snippet: On an unexpectedly warm November day, lunch outdoors meant takeout, brown-bag fare and a good view.
lead_paragraph: By all rights, the narrow public plaza carved out of Broadway between 38th and 39th Streets should have been empty last week beyond the scurrying city walkers, their jackets buttoned and their collars turned high against a damp November chill. But Monday was an unseasonable 70 and sunny, and the makeshift pedestrian mall, with its tiny chairs and tables, was the perfect place to enjoy what easily might have been the last outdoor lunch of the year.

abstract: Despite the many flight cancellations in recent days, the slowing economy, rising gas prices and the weak dollar, the number of air travelers is holding steady so far this year.
snippet: Despite the many flight cancellations in recent days, the slowing economy, rising gas prices and the weak dollar, the number of air travelers is holding steady so far this year.
lead_paragraph: Nina Rubin, who is in public relations in Atlanta, is going back to the Berkshires this summer but is hoping to save money on her plane ticket by flying into a smaller airport. abstract: Despite Wall Street's widespread skepticism about the merger of Symantec and Veritas Software, shareholders of the two companies approved the deal on Friday.     The deal, which is valued at just under $11 billion and combines two companies with vastly different strategies, would create the fifth-largest software company. The final value of the transaction will not be known until the deal officially closes on July 2.
